199%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66216199.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66216199.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Textile%20Exports%20Shrink%2C%20Mills%20Facing%20Cash%20Crunch%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16190654%2Fjanko-ferlic-eBtwD6ZG78I-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20textile%20and%20apparel%20industry%20saw%20an%2011.3%25%20reduction%20in%20exports%20in%20June%202023%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%20while%20several%20mills%20continue%20to%20face%20acute%20cash%20loss%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2Ftextile-exports-continue-to-decline-in-june-mills-suspend-work-on-tepid-demand%2Farticle67084560.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Several%20mills%20in%20the%20South%20also%20suspended%20production%20citing%20lack%20of%20demand%2C%20the%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExport%20of%20cotton%20yarn%2C%20fabrics%2C%20made-ups%20and%20handloom%20products%20slid%20by%201.21%25%20year-on-year%20(y-o-y)%2C%20shipment%20of%20man%20made%20products%20saw%20a%2017.22%20%25%20decline%20while%20jute%20products%20and%20carpets%20plunged%20by%2026.72%20%25%20and%2015.43%25%20respectively%2C%20according%20to%20data%20shared%20by%20the%20Confederation%20of%20Indian%20Textile%20Industry%20(CITI).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETextile%20exports%20in%20June%202023%20were%20worth%20%241%2C624%20million%20(%241%2C736%20million%20in%20June%202022)%20while%20apparel%20exports%20were%20worth%20%241%2C248%20million%20as%20opposed%20to%20%241%2C501%20million%20last%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESiddhartha%20Rajagopal%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20Cotton%20Textiles%20Export%20Promotion%20Council%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2Ftextile-exports-continue-to-decline-in-june-mills-suspend-work-on-tepid-demand%2Farticle67084560.ece%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHindu%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20export%20of%20cotton%20products%20was%20expected%20to%20pick%20up%20in%20the%20next%20two%20months%20as%20the%20month-on-month%20rate%20of%20decline%20had%20reduced%20in%20June.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20smaller%20textile%20mills%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20were%20suspending%20production%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20orders%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20K.M.%20Subramanian%2C%20president%20of%20Tiruppur%20Exporters%20Association%2C%20said%20the%20smaller%20companies%20were%20the%20worst%20affected%20in%20the%20Tiruppur%20cluster.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFactors%20such%20as%20slowdown%20in%20the%20U.S.%20and%20EU%20and%20lack%20of%20cost%20competitiveness%20were%20affecting%20textile%20and%20clothing%20exports.%20The%20yarn%20that%20should%20be%20exported%20is%20coming%20into%20the%20domestic%20market.%20There%20is%20already%20excess%20capacity%20in%20the%20country.%20These%20were%20among%20the%20factors%20affecting%20the%20textile%20industry%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2Ftextile-exports-continue-to-decline-in-june-mills-suspend-work-on-tepid-demand%2Farticle67084560.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20CITI%20chairman%20T.%20Rajkumar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERavi%20Sam%2C%20chairman%20of%20Southern%20India%20Mills%E2%80%99%20Association%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20free%20trade%20agreement%20with%20the%20UK%20would%20grant%20immediate%20relief%20to%20the%20Indian%20textile%20industry.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20expensive%20because%20of%209%25%20to%2011%25%20duty%20in%20the%20UK%20market.%20If%20India%20gets%20duty-free%20access%2C%20th