20a%20young%20teenager%2C%20he%20began%20working%20as%20an%20interpreter%20for%20the%20US%20military.%20He%20later%20met%20his%20wife%20and%20they%20had%20three%20of%20their%20four%20children.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Afghanistan%20government%20fell%20in%202021%2C%20the%20United%20States%20fled%2C%20and%20the%20Taliban%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-must-evacuate-thousands-from-afghanistan-amid-taliban-isis-threats-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ere-captured%3C%2Fa%3E%20Kabul%2C%20he%20and%20his%20family%20had%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20flee.%20After%20several%20frantic%20months%2C%20they%20made%20it%20out%20of%20Taliban-controlled%20Afghanistan%20and%20%E2%80%94eventually%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20United%20States.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20on%20July%203%2C%20Ahmad%20Yar%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fdc-md-va%2F2023%2F07%2F08%2Fnasrat-ahmadyar-lyft-driver-killed-dc%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efatally%20shot%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%20while%20driving%20for%20Lyft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20uniquely%20tragic%20American%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20Yar%20selflessly%20dedicated%20himself%20to%20helping%20others%2C%20his%20loved%20ones%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0Matthew%20Butler%20%E2%80%94%20an%20Army%20Special%20Forces%20veteran%20who%20served%20two%20tours%20in%20Afghanistan%20with%20Ahmad%20Yar%20as%20his%20interpreter%20%E2%80%94%20said%20he%20first%20showed%20up%20at%20a%20US%20camp%20in%20Afghanistan%20as%20a%20young%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe'd%20been%20hanging%20out%20at%20this%20camp%20since%20he%20was%2010%20years%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20Butler%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAt%20first%2C%20they%20just%20paid%20him%20to%20empty%20the%20trash%20or%20rake%20rocks.%20Ultimately%2C%20he%20taught%20himself%20English%20through%20association.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20Yar%20and%20his%20family%20first%20set%20their%20eyes%20on%20coming%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%202020.%20However%2C%20Ahmad%20Yar's%20plans%20were%20immediately%20derailed%20after%20the%20Afghanistan%20government%20fell%20in%202021%20and%20the%20Taliban%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-must-evacuate-thousands-from-afghanistan-amid-taliban-isis-threats-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaptured%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20city%20of%20Kabul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20Butler%20%E2%80%94%20now%20Ahmad%20Yar's%20close%20friend%20%E2%80%94%20immediately%20began%20mobilizing%20resources%20within%20the%20veteran%20community%20to%20make%20sure%20he%20could%20leave%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20probably%20exchanged%20a%20couple%20hundred%20text%20messages%20a%20day%20for%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20Butler%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20my%20full-time%20job%2C%20keeping%20him%20alive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20Yar%20was%20just%20one%20of%20hundreds%20of%20Afghan%20interpreters%20scrambling%20to%20flee%20the%20country%20after%20the%20Taliban%20takeover.%20Their%20work%20for%20the%20US%20military%20put%20them%20in%20significant%20danger%20of%20being%20targeted%20by%20Taliban%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20requires%20interpreters%20like%20Ahmad%20Yar%20to%20apply%20for%20Special%20Immigrant%20Visas%2C%20which%20allow%20foreign%20nationals%20who%20have%20worked%20for%20the%20US%20government%20to%20immigrate.%20Throughout%202022%2C%20many%20investigations%20%E2%80%94%20including%20those%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fworld-nation%2Fstory%2F2022-10-02%2Fafghan-interpreters-blacklisted-special-immigrant-visas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELA%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2022%2F12%2F28%2Fpolitics%2Fafghan-interpreter-marines-special-i