0Sunday%20(July%2016)%20at%20her%20home%20in%20Paris%2C%20according%20to%20Le%20Parisien%20newspaper.%20She%20was%2076.%20Birkin%20was%20best%20known%20internationally%20for%20her%20steamy%201969%20duet%20%E2%80%9CJe%20t%E2%80%99aime%E2%80%A6%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Patrick%20Frater%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fjane-birkin-dead-british-french-actor-singer-1235671263%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fjane-birkin-dead-british-french-actor-singer-1235671263%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fjane-birkin-dead-british-french-actor-singer-1235671263%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Japan%20to%20Release%201.3%20Million%20Tonnes%20of%20Water%20Used%20During%20Fukushima%20Nuclear%20Accident%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16173220%2F3e08d767-76b2-473f-b4a9-c602b2f3a53e.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20go%20for%20a%20swim%20in%20an%20ocean%20they%20are%20literally%20bathing%20in%20a%20sea%20of%20natural%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20predominant%20component%20of%20the%20radiation%20comes%20from%20potassium-40%20which%20is%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnicerlab.ldeo.columbia.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fcontent%2FPublication%2FWang_etal2020.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enatural%20part%20of%20the%20earth%E2%80%99s%20environment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhal.science%2Fhal-02336283%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETritium%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20heavy%20cousin%20of%20hydrogen%2C%20and%20carbon-14%20are%20also%20sources%20produced%20when%20high-energy%20protons%20from%20space%20smash%20into%20oxygen%20and%20nitrogen%20atoms%20in%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20atmospheric%20source%20of%20ocean%20radioactivity%20has%20worked%20on%20Earth%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41561-020-0538-9%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealmost%20three%20billion%20years%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Along%20with%20uranium%20radioactive%20decay%20products%2C%20humans%20live%20within%20this%20natural%20radioactive%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20the%20Japanese%20government%20plans%20to%20release%201.3%20million%20tonnes%20of%20water%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eused%20to%20cool%20the%20damaged%20reactor%20cores%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20accident%20in%20March%202011%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20into%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202011-2013%2C%20approximately%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20110516154816%2Fhttp%3A%2Fwww.asahi.com%2Fenglish%2FTKY201105120189.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E300%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20untreated%20wastewater%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0had%20already%20flowed%20into%20the%20ocean%20off%20Fukushima.%20These%20first%20two%20years%20were%20the%20most%20dangerous%20time%20because%20long-lived%20heavy%20nuclei%2C%20like%20cesium-137%2C%20strontium-90%20and%20shorter-lived%20iodine-131%2C%20from%20nuclear%20fission%20in%20the%20reactors%20ended%20up%20in%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202013%2C%20the%20stored%20water%20has%20also%20accumulated%20flushed%20seawater%20goundwater%20which%20leaked%20into%20the%20three%20damaged%20reactor%20cores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20challenge%20is%20how%20to%20manage%201.3%20million%20tonnes%20of%20unsafe%20radioactively-tainted%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20three%20options%20was%20to%20filter%20out%20the%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%2C%20then%20dump%20the%20filtered%20water%20into%20the%20ocean%20to%20dilute%20any%20remaining%20amount%20of%20tritium%20or%20carbon-14.%20%C2%A0Japan%20has%20chosen%20this%20complex%20way%20from%20all%20the%20fraught%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisposing%20of%20untreated%20wastewater%20into%20the%20ocean%20would%20release%20nuclear%20fission%20products%20in%20an%20uncontrolled%20manner.%20The%20danger%20of%20indiscriminately%20releasing%20nuclear%20fission%20products%20into%20the%20ocean%20is%20that%20the%20products%20can%20find%20their%20way%20into%20the%20food%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20the%20nuclear%20fission%20heavy%20nuclei%20like%20cesium-137%2C%20strontium-90%20and%20iodine-131%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fscience%2Farticles%2F2011%2F06%2F21%2F3245821.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econcentrate%20in%20human%20muscle%2C%20bones%2C%20and%20thyroid%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20cause%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioline.org.br%2Fpdf%3Fja07057%5C%22%3ECancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20Japan%20planned%20to%20remove%20as%20much%20of%20these%20radioactive%20nuclei%20as%20possible%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20water%20before%20its%20release.%20Some%20cesium-137%20and%20strontium-90%20%C2%A0nuclei%20already%20exist%20on%20the%20ocean%20floor%20due%20to%20nuclear%20weapons%20tests%20in%20the%201950s%20and%2060s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20good%20guide%20for%20having%20confidence%20in%20the%20safe%20release%20of%20radiation%20is%20to%20reduce%20human%20radiation%20exposure%20by%20making%20it%20%E2%80%9CAs%20Low%20As%20Reasonably%20Achievable%E2%80%9D%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Fradiation%2Falara.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EALARA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiltering%20out%20the%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%20from%20the%20stored%20wastewater%20may%20be%20the%20best%20that%20can%20be%20done.The%20ALARA%20approach%20to%20reduce%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%20released%20resulted%20in%20a%202013%20effort%20to%20develop%20and%20employ%20an%20advanced%20liquid%20processing%20system%2C%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tepco.co.jp%2Fen%2Fnu%2Ffukushima-np%2Fhandouts%2F2013%2Fimages%2Fhandouts_130329_01-e.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EALPS%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20series%20of%20filters%20was%20designed%20to%20remove%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freport_1_review_mission_to_tepco_and_meti.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E62%20fission%20nuclei%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0leaving%20both%20tritium%20and%20carbon-14%20in%20the%20water.%20%C2%A0It%20only%20partially%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tokyo%20Electric%20Power%20company%20(TEPCO)%20and%20the%20International%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20(IAEA)%20agree%20that%20about%2070%25%20of%20the%20stored%20Fukushima%20water%20may%20still%20carry%20some%20of%20the%20original%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei.%20Potentially%2C%20this%20water%20could%20be%20run%20through%20more%20cycles%20of%20the%20ALPS%20before%20extra%20dilution%20and%20later%20release%20into%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%2030%25%20of%20treated%20water%20could%20also%20be%20diluted%20with%20seawater%20by%20factors%20of%20several%20hundred%20to%20one%20thousand%20and%20then%20released%20into%20the%20ocean.%20Any%20remaining%20tritium%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20reactor%20may%20find%20its%20way%20into%20the%20food%20chain%20as%20organically%20bound%20tritium%20via%20build-up%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0025326X0100039X%3Fcasa_token%3DrU1zVGEdYYMAAAAA%3ArO5YwPfC1BWdCjRSA2hjh38Vm0LPcBd79Gg42kaVhE76hroYTnj7zEaLPRyiXmn32TGX4yqK%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eunderwater%20plants%20and%20organisms%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganically%20bound%20tritium%20will%20still%20keep%20its%2012.4-year%20half-life%2C%20but%20these%20nuclei%20stay%20in%20the%20human%20body%20for%20roughly%2010%20days%20before%20half%20of%20their%20number%20is%20excreted.%20The%2010%20days%20is%20known%20as%20the%20biological%20half-life%20of%20tritium.%20The%20process%20for%20excreting%20carbon-14%20has%20a%20biological%20half-life%20of%20about%2040%20days%2C%20which%20is%20negligible%20compared%20to%20its%205%2C730-year%20radioactive%20decay%20half-life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20short%20biological%20half-lives%20contrast%20sharply%20with%20the%20decades-long%20residence%20time%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fradiation%2Fradionuclide-basics-cesium-137%23cesiumhealth%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecesium-137%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fradiation%2Fradionuclide-basics-strontium-90%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estrontium-90%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0inside%20the%20human%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20option%20for%20managing%20the%20Fukushima%20water%20was%20to%20hold%20it%20on%20site%20in%20an%20ever-increasing%20number%20of%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20water%20is%20properly%20filtered%20to%20leave%20only%20tritium%20and%20carbon-14%2C%20then%20the%20natural%20decay%20of%20tritium%20can%20be%20used%20to%20reduce%20overall%20radioactivity.%20%C2%A0Since%20the%20radioactive%20half-life%20of%20tritium%20is%2012.4%20years%2C%20holding%20the%20water%20in%20tanks%20for%20seven%20half-lives%2C%20about%2085%20years%2C%20would%20reduce%20the%20tritium%20content%20to%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20its%20current%20value.%20This%20option%20leaves%20the%20carbon-14%20which%20would%20still%20roughly%20have%20the%20same%20radioactivity%20due%20to%20its%205%2C730-year%20half-life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20storing%20a%20tremendous%20volume%20of%20water%20for%20an%20entire%20human%20lifespan%20has%20never%20been%20tried.%20Even%20more%20water%20and%20storage%20tanks%20would%20need%20to%20be%20added%20as%20decommissioning%20the%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20nuclear%20reactor%20cores%20proceeds.%20This%20is%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20third%20option%20was%20to%20evaporate%20the%20water%20on%20land%20near%20Fukushima.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201979%20nuclear%20accident%20at%20Three%20Mile%20Island%20Nuclear%20Station%20in%20the%20United%20States%20resulted%20in%20a%20similar%20radioactive%20water%20storage%20problem.%20About%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcollections.digitalmaryland.org%2Fdigital%2Fapi%2Fcollection%2Fsaac%2Fid%2F42040%2Fdownload%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E9%2C300%20tonnes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20tritiated%20water%2C%20about%20140%20times%20less%20than%20that%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20Fukushima%20storage%20tanks%2C%20was%20electrically%20evaporated%20over%20two%20years.%20The%20tritium%20was%20released%20into%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20radiation%20dose%20to%20people%20in%20the%20surrounding%20area%20of%20about%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrc.gov%2Freading-rm%2Fdoc-collections%2Ffact-sheets%2F3mile-isle.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone-hundredth%20of%20the%20natural%20background%20radiation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan%20and%20TEPCO%20would%20need%20to%20deal%20with%20even%20larger%20amounts%20of%20water%20and%20tritium%20emitted%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20if%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freport_1_review_mission_to_tepco_and_meti.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E30-year%20timeline%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20reactor%20core%20clean-up%20is%20followed.%20Again%2C%20this%20option%20was%20too%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20crucial%20to%20distinguish%20natural%20background%20radiation%20from%20that%20of%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%20when%20seeking%20to%20understand%20the%20choice%20made%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Ffeb%2F15%2Ffukushima-japan-insists-release-of-treated-water-is-safe-nuclear-disaster%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJapan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20supported%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Ftopics%2Fresponse%2Ffukushima-daiichi-nuclear-accident%2Ffukushima-daiichi-alps-treated-water-discharge%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EIAEA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nobody%20wants%20to%20add%20additional%20radiation%20to%20the%20oceans%2C%20if%20only%20because%20of%20sympathy%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2019%2Fsep%2F16%2Ffukushima-fisherman-fear-for-future-over-release-of-radioactive-water%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elocal%20Fukushima%20fishers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20proper%20ALPS%20filtering%2C%20people%20who%20go%20out%20to%20swim%20in%20the%20ocean%20should%20still%20have%20radiation%20exposure%20as%20the%20least%20of%20their%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20David%20Krofcheck%20is%20a%20Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Physics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Auckland.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20orginally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2Fa-deep-dive-into-the-reality-of-radioactive-water%2F%5C%22%3E360News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689511169000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16173220%2F3e08d767-76b2-473f-b4a9-c602b2f3a53e.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-to-release-1-3-million-tonnes-of-water-used-during-fukushima-nuclear-accident%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20water%20used%20to%20cool%20damaged%20reactor%20cores%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20accident%20in%20March%202011.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-to-release-1-3-million-tonnes-of-water-used-during-fukushima-nuclear-accident%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bhumi%20channels%20her%20inner%20'Barbie'%20-%20View%20pics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689510004000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101802240%2Cimgsize-55412.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fbhumi-pednekar-wins-the-internet-as-she-channels-her-inner-barbie-pics-insid