trafficking%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20cooperation%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cearly%20return%20of%20trafficked%20victims%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20a%201%2C643%20kilometre%20long%20border%20with%20Myanmar%20which%20runs%20along%20four%20states%20in%20the%20north%20east.%20Due%20to%20its%20proximity%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20sensitive%20northeastern%20region%2C%20there%20have%20been%20concerns%20about%20the%20military%20junta%E2%80%99s%20actions%20which%20drive%20refugees%20across%20the%20border%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasiatimes.com%2F2021%2F12%2Fmyanmar-military-joining-hands-with-indian-rebels%2F%5C%22%3Einconsistent%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fmyanmar-army-abandons-taga-headquarters-of-northeast-insurgent-groups-after-three-years-5450287.html%5C%22%3Eattitude%3C%2Fa%3E%20towards%20insurgent%20groups.%20Over%2050%2C000%20refugees%20are%20estimated%20to%20have%20fled%20across%20into%20India%20following%20the%20junta%E2%80%99s%20crackdown%20after%20the%202021%20coup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20also%20noted%20that%20India%20was%20%E2%80%9Cconcerned%20about%20the%20humanitarian%20situation%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%9D%20and%20proposed%20%E2%80%9Cpeople-centric%20initiatives%20aimed%20to%20address%20the%20pressing%20challenges%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20other%20neighbours%2C%20India%20has%20remained%20engaged%20with%20the%20military%20junta%20after%20the%20February%202021%20coup%2C%20though%20New%20Delhi%20has%20also%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20democracy%20at%20all%20political%20encounters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20again%20stated%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9Csupports%20the%20democratic%20transition%20process%20in%20Myanmar%20and%20highlights%20the%20need%20for%20return%20of%20peace%20and%20stability%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20reiterated%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9Cclosely%20coordinates%20our%20policy%20with%20ASEAN%20in%20this%20regard%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20was%20earlier%20in%20Indonesia%20where%20ASEAN%20foreign%20ministers%20re-endorsed%20the%20five-point%20consensus.%20However%2C%20the%20Myanmar%20foreign%20minister%20was%20barred%20from%20attending%20the%20conference%20as%20the%20junta%20had%20failed%20to%20meet%20its%20commitments%20under%20the%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThailand%20deviated%20from%20the%20collective%20approach%20of%20ASEAN%20when%20its%20foreign%20minister%20Don%20Pramudwinai%2C%20visited%20Myanmar%20and%20met%20with%20the%20detained%20ousted%20leader%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20held%20by%20the%20military%20junta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20seems%20to%20be%20aligning%20with%20the%20Thai%20initiative%20to%20have%20a%20separate%20channel%20of%20engagement%20since%20the%20ASEAN%20method%20seems%20to%20have%20stalled.%20In%20June%2C%20India%20had%20taken%20part%20in%20a%20meeting%20hosted%20by%20Thailand%20of%20neighbouring%20countries%20and%20Myanmar%2C%20which%20had%20seen%20three%20major%20ASEAN%20countries%20rebuff%20the%20Thai%20invitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20on%20the%20connectivity%20issue%2C%20India%20conveyed%20that%20it%20was%20important%20to%20expedite%20projects%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20have%20faced%20challenges%20in%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20especially%20the%20India-Myanmar-Thailand%20trilateral%20highway%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1680530471355031556%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20MGC%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jaishankar%20again%20raised%20the%20issue%20implementing%20the%20much-delayed%20trilateral%20highway%20and%20also%20concluding%20the%20motor%20vehicle%20agreement%20between%20the%20three%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689507952000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16165045%2FF1IaVFRaMAAZEtQ.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2F