high-at-rs-1-4-trn-in-may-rbi-data-123071600254_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fcredit-card-spending-hits-record-high-at-rs-1-4-trn-in-may-rbi-data-123071600254_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fcredit-card-spending-hits-record-high-at-rs-1-4-trn-in-may-rbi-data-123071600254_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wheat%20Auctions%20Fail%20to%20Reduce%20Retail%20Prices%2C%20Government%20Bars%20Traders%20From%20Participating%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F19140932%2F6853779020_9b69a0d246_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20will%20not%20allow%20traders%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20next%20round%20of%20wheat%20e-auction%20scheduled%20for%20July%2019%20after%20learning%20that%20its%20open%20market%20sale%20policy%20has%20not%20resulted%20in%20reduction%20of%20sale%20prices%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fagri-business%2Fgovt-bars-traders-in-wheat-auction-lowers-quantity-in-next-round%2Farticle67083715.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20scheme%2C%20which%20was%20started%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20controlling%20food%20prices%2C%20has%20only%20helped%20middlemen%20make%20a%20profit%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quantity%20offered%20for%20sale%20has%20also%20been%20reduced%20by%2056%25%20from%204.18%20lakh%20tonnes%20in%20the%20last%20round%20to%201.83%20lakh%20tonnes%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2012%2C%20food%20secretary%20Sanjeev%20Chopra%20had%20announced%20the%20plan%20to%20sell%2015%20lakh%20tonnes%20of%20wheat%20from%20the%20central%20pool%20stock%20in%20the%20first%20phase%20and%20said%20that%20it%20would%20be%20raised%20further%20if%20required%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20open%20market%20scheme%E2%80%99s%20main%20objective%20is%20to%20increase%20the%20availability%20of%20grains%20and%20reduce%20its%20retail%20price.%20While%20the%20quantity%20of%20wheat%20sold%20in%20each%20round%20increased%2C%20prices%20did%20not%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wheat%20offtake%20was%2021%25%20in%20the%20first%20round%20and%2042%25%20in%20the%20third%20round%20of%20auction%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20data%20maintained%20by%20the%20consumer%20affairs%20ministry%2C%20the%20all-India%20average%20retail%20price%20of%20wheat%20increased%20from%20Rs%2031.27%2Fkg%20in%20May%20to%20Rs%2031.67%2Fkg%20in%20June%20and%20the%20average%20price%20in%20July%20has%20further%20shot%20up%20to%20Rs%2031.99%2Fkg.%20Similarly%2C%20%3Cem%3Eatta%3C%2Fem%3E%20prices%20were%20Rs%2036.42%2Fkg%20in%20May%2C%20Rs%2036.95%2Fkg%20in%20June%20and%20Rs%2037.16%2Fkg%20during%20July%201-14.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20change%20in%20the%20guidelines%20was%20necessitated%20after%20the%20results%20of%20the%20third%20round%20showed%20an%20increase%20in%20average%20rate%20despite%20the%20claim%20of%20allowing%20actual%20users%E2%80%99%20participation%20through%20the%20capping%20clause%20at%20100%20tonnes.%20Unless%20the%20government%20addresses%20the%20basic%20issue%20of%20higher%20physical%20availability%20in%20the%20market%20more%20realistically%2C%20and%20not%20through%20policing%20methods%20like%20stock%20limit%2C%20the%20prices%20may%20not%20be%20contained%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20industry%20expert%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20sold%20out%20price%20in%20the%20e-auctions%20also%20rose%20from%20Rs%202%2C136%20and%20Rs%202%2C137%20per%20quintal%20in%20the%20first%20two%20rounds%20to%20Rs%202%2C150%2Fquintal%20in%20the%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20highest%20selling%20rate%20of%20Rs%202%2C245%2Fquintal%2